This is the third alert issued by the US embassy in Mali since March 2021. The latest advisory came days after 22 civilians were killed in Mali's northern Menaka region by suspected militants. Malian media reported that armed men who staged the attack were affiliated to the Islamic State group. Mali's military-led government heightened security in Bamako after militant killed six soldiers in the central Mopti region on April 24. The rising insecurity in northern Mali has been attributed to the withdrawal of French forces from the country. --BBC--